The environment describes a simultaneous application/identification mechanism where matches occur via closed loops (S -> H -> S' -> H' -> ... -> S). This mechanism, while distinct from standard Deferred Acceptance (DA), often exhibits similar stability properties and can be strategically manipulated by the proposing side (students) if the resulting stable matching is not unique or if the resolution of conflicts depends on the application order.
